SEC staff has agreed in principle to dismiss its unlawful enforcement case =
against Coinbase, subject to Commissioner approval =E2=80=93 righting a maj=
or wrong. We=E2=80=99ve always maintained [ https://substack.com/redirect/4=
a065e92-d193-4de1-9ea4-d4dacb168165?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] that we were right on the facts and the law, =
and today=E2=80=99s announcement confirms that this case should never have =
been filed in the first place. This is a victory not just for Coinbase, but=
 for our customers, the United States, and individual freedom.
Big win for crypto!
The SEC has agreed to drop its lawsuit against Coinbase, pending commission=
er approval. This case was a particularly frustrating one for anyone involv=
ed in crypto =E2=80=94the SEC had previously reviewed and approved Coinbase=
=E2=80=99s business model when it went public in 2021 but then sued the com=
pany in 2023 without any changes to its operations. The case, which was bro=
ught forth under Gary Gensler=E2=80=99s SEC, was pretty obviously political=
ly motivated and a blatant example of the the SEC=E2=80=99s broader anti-cr=
ypto agenda.
The crypto industry, especially the larger companies like Coinbase, want cl=
ear crypto guidelines and regulations =E2=80=94 they want certainty that th=
eir businesses could not overnight be the target of overreaching and vague =
regulation. It must be extremely frustrating to run a business that, at any=
 point, could be the victim of politically motivated regulation. The SEC=E2=
=80=99s dropping of the lawsuit signals that those days of vagueness are ov=
er.
(7) Humanity has THREE lunar landers heading to the moon right now [ https:=
//substack.com/redirect/ebfae98e-f89d-4a81-aa69-080b15a1d814?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Christian Keil on X
