c316-4312-a462-c27cdb389b41?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
We are so back. Literally. To the moon. Literally. Like =E2=80=9CWe are so =
back to the moon.=E2=80=9D
As we speak, three private companies=E2=80=94Intuitive Machines, Firefly Ae=
rospace, and ispace=E2=80=94have lunar landers en route to the moon. Until =
Intuitive Machines=E2=80=99 Odysseus lander touched down near the lunar sou=
th pole a year ago, no American craft had landed on Luna since 1972. 1972! =
Fifty-three years!=20
Now, in 2025, two American craft and one Japanese are on their way.=20
Firefly Aerospace's Blue Ghost mission, launched on January 15, 2025, is pa=
rt of NASA=E2=80=99s Commercial Lunar Payload Services (CLPS) program, whic=
h wants to establish a steady flow of robotic missions to the moon.=20
Intuitive Machines launched its second lunar lander, IM-2 (Athena) on Wedne=
sday aboard a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket, heading for a planned landing at Mons=
 Mouton near the moon=E2=80=99s south pole. The lander is mostly carrying e=
quipment use to drill for water ice, some smaller lunar rovers, and some co=
mmunications equipment. This is also a CLPs program, and along with Firefly=
, a great example of public<>private<>private partnership between NASA, Spa=
ceX, and Intuitive Machines/Firefly.
Japan=E2=80=99s ispace Resilience lander, which also hitched a SpaceX ride =
on January 15, 2025, is not part of the CLPS program but has been selected =
for a future CLPS mission.
Today, the moon. Tomorrow? Mars=E2=80=A6which may be showing more signs of =
life [ https://substack.com/redirect/dd151fad-f27a-469a-971d-3ff6e47a421f?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] than pr=
eviously thought.
We=E2=80=99re even brining things back from space. Not Boring Capital portf=
olio company Varda=E2=80=99s W-2 spacecraft [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/13496172-2fbf-455d-a00a-ed61cf6738fa?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=9Csuccessfully executed its final re=
entry burn and is preparing to deorbit=E2=80=9D and will land in Australia =
in the coming days. We=E2=80=99ll keep you posted, but in the meantime, ple=
ase enjoy this shot of W-2 streaking across the night sky [ https://substac=
k.com/redirect/cb816b5d-8078-43a0-9b23-cc49c2122e02?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.=
gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=20
What a beautiful universe we get to explore.=20
Have a great weekend y=E2=80=99all.
